text: Old store building along Route M in Jamesville The cemetery at Jamesville at the intersection of Routes M and U Jamesville is an unincorporated community in northeast Stone County, Missouri, United States.Geographic Names Information System (GNIS), USGS The community is located just west of the confluence of Finley Creek and the James River, along Missouri Route M.Highlandville Missouri 7.5 Minute Topographic Quad, USGS, 1955Missouri Atlas & Gazetteer, DeLorme, 1998, First edition, p. 62, The historic Jamesville School was located along Finley Creek to the east of the settlement.Jamesville school locationJamesville School historical reference ==References== ==External links== * Historic Jamesville, Missouri: A Personal Perspective Video by MSU (Aired: 12/18/2011) * Hootentown Bridge, James River at Jamesville - Library of Congress Category:Unincorporated communities in Stone County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
